mastering git:
steps:
 // creating repo
 1. still in terminal(read 1-git-note-getting start)
 2. mkdir hs-website
 3. cd hs-website
 4. git status
 5. git init


 info:
 - repository(repo) is a place to store something
 - a git repo stores files and keeps track of any changes called
   version control system ~ to able to keep track of all changes
   see whos made them and if needed(issues) people can revert into
   a previous version
 - it can integrate with a lot of people at same time without the need
   of extra works
